    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/47253</id>
    <published>2011-04-15T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2011-04-15T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/diplomatic-influence-value-fund-reuniting-europe"/>
    <title>Diplomatic Influence &amp; Value Fund - Reuniting Europe</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Reuniting Europe programme supports partner countries with the 
reforms necessary for EU accession or closer partnership with the EU.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It focuses on: * stable institutions * guaranteeing 
democracy * the rule of law * human rights * the respect for and 
protection of minorities&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Further details of the rationale behind the selection of these 
objectives and guidelines on the kinds of projects sought are contained 
in the Diplomatic Influence and Values (DIV) Fund 2011/12.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
