    <id>tag:www.gov.uk,2005:PublicationesquePresenter/55282</id>
    <published>2010-06-30T00:00:00+01:00</published>
    <updated>2010-06-30T00:00:00+01:00</updated>
    <link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/freedom-of-religion-or-belief-how-the-fco-can-help-promote-respect-for-this-human-right"/>
    <title>Freedom of Religion or Belief - how the FCO can help promote respect for this human right</title>
    <content type="html">&lt;div class="govspeak"&gt;&lt;p&gt;Freedom of religion or belief is a human right whose enjoyment is important to achieving the UK’s strategic priorities, particularly as regards conflict prevention and resolution. It is a sensitive issue in many countries. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;These guidelines, elaborated with the help of specialist stakeholders, aim to provide a simple introduction to the issues for FCO posts and desks, some responses to frequently raised issues, and other resources for those who wish to go deeper into the subject.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</content>
